White Rock lake, sunset bay near the pier
Another Winter Visitor
Song sparrows raise their babies in Canada and the northern states.  In the winter they show up here and stay all winter.  A very handsome bird, they seem to play peek-a-boo in the low bushes, it is rare for me to find one perched in the open like this one.
